<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12057b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12057b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12057b"> 57(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> commonwealth <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>republic<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> of / letters</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Ce fut &eacute;galement sous le r&egrave;gne de Louis XV que fut enferm&eacute; au Mont un jeune homme du nom de Desforges, auquel on reprochait d&apos;avoir &eacute;crit un libelle violent contre le roi et la Cour. Il fut ret&eacute;nu au Mont plusieurs ann&eacute;es. Bachaumont, dans ses <cite>M&eacute;moires Secrets</cite> <font color="green">[162]</font> s&apos;exprime ainsi: &laquo;La r&eacute;publique des Lettres vient de perdre le sieur Desforges, mort il y a quelques jours, subitement, &agrave; table. C&apos;&eacute;tait un auteur, moins c&eacute;l&egrave;bre par ses opuscules que par ses malheurs. <font color="green">[&hellip;.]</font>&raquo; <br><font color="green">[It was also in the reign of Louis XV that a young man was imprisoned on the Mont under the name of Desforges who was accused of a violent libel against the king and the Court. He was held on the Mont for several years. Bachaumont, in his <cite>M&eacute;moires Secrets</cite> puts it this way: &ldquo;The <mark>republic of Letters</mark> has lost monsieur Desforges, died suddenly a couple of days ago, at dinner. He was a writer, less famous for his work than for his bad luck. [&hellip;]</font>] <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 162-3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
